This article is on reddit which answers questions. - How to access folder containing Wordpress on your Lightsail instance.
I was not sure which folder the wordpress root folder was located in aws. This helped me understand the file to locate the wp-content 
folder: /opt/bitnami/apps/wordpress/htdocs/wp-content/themes

The link below guided me to connect to my wordpress root directory. I needed to do this to upload my child theme with css file. 

https://lightsail.aws.amazon.com/ls/docs/en_us/articles/amazon-lightsail-connecting-to-linux-unix-instance-using-sftp#connecting-
to-linux-unix-instance-using-sftp-prerequisites

